  <section>
    <h2>Summary Overview</h2>
    <p>This theme covers machine learning systems where structure, grounding, and deployment constraints matter. The work spans graph-conditioned language models, multi-agent enterprise question answering, token-budget-aware graph retrieval, multi-modal recommendation, business-insight generation, agreement frameworks for LLM agents, typicality for information retrieval, and resource-aware deep learning.</p>
    <p>The common thread is making AI systems more inspectable, evidence-aware, efficient, and useful in settings where model behavior has to connect to knowledge, decisions, and operational constraints.</p>
  </section>

